# Meta provider (jumon-mcp)

## Platform id

`meta` — gateway provider segment and `explore_platform` platform name.

## Tools

34 read tools — see [docs/meta-ads-tools.md](../../docs/meta-ads-tools.md).

Prefer **`meta_search_ad_entities`** for performance questions (`level: adset|ad`); structure lists + `meta_get_*` for navigation.

## File map

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `tools.go` | Registration |
| `schemas.go`, `schema_docs.go` | Agent schemas + docs |
| `inputs.go`, `graph_query.go` | Parse + encode Graph query |
| `graph_batch.go` | Graph Batch API (delivery errors) |
| `pagination.go` | `auto_paginate` |
| `accounts.go`, `structure.go`, `insights.go`, `delivery.go`, `pages.go` | Core service methods |
| `field_context.go`, `field_catalog_data.go` | Embedded field catalog |
| `creatives.go`, `media.go`, `targeting.go`, `audiences.go`, `intelligence.go` | P3/P4 tools |
| `measurement.go`, `activities.go` | R1/R2 measurement + audit trail |
| `graph_errors.go`, `proxy.go` | Error parsing + gateway port (GET + POST form) |

## Conventions

- Prefix `meta_`. Normalize `act_id` to `act_` in parsers.
- All calls via `gateway.Client` — never hold tokens in Go.
- Graph query: pre-encode JSON params (`filtering`, `time_range`, `targeting_spec`) as strings in query map.
- Graph Batch: POST form `batch` JSON array via `postFormWithRefresh`.
- API version **v25.0** in descriptions; authoritative env in mcp-ads-manager.

## Do not

- Call Graph API directly from Go.
- Expose top-level MCP tools (register in internal registry only).
- Add Meta-specific gateway routes.
- Ship Ad Library tools (`ads_archive`).
- Register `meta_search_behaviors`, `meta_search_demographics`, or `meta_get_dataset_stats` until `ads_read` Advanced Access is approved (see Paused tools in meta-ads-tools.md).
